So many great bars downtown. DON'T BOTHER with this one!  Stopped in here during GenCon to get a quick drink and maybe something to eat. Sat down at the bar in a mostly empty room. Noticed the floor was unusually sticky. Meh, it's a music bar not a place with class, whatever. Received a drink from the most disinterested bartender I have ever seen. He did not acknowledge me. Barely looked at me. Didn't string two words together. I can understand in a packed bar being distracted or having some kind of an excuse, but there was absolutely nothing. Two groups at the far end of the bar and a server eating her dinner before the rush hit. He didn't even ask if I wanted a food menu. I would tell you his name, but neither he nor I cared enough to get to know each other, all I know is he had a pencil behind his ear.  Shortly after I received a beer, a small bachelorette party came in. Their arrival pointed out how sticky the floor was as one of the cheap laminate "boards" quite literally came up attached to her shoe. One would think a bartender with any sense at all would start catering to a bigger group which came in, nope. He was as disinterested in them as he was me. The only tip this bartender deserves is to find another job because he is wasting everyone's time and doing an already sketchy bar a massive disservice.  The girls got drinks and wandered off to a table, I ordered a second drink which he poured like a moron resulting in an overflow of foam and only a 3/4's full plastic cup. While I dealt with his mess a guy came up to the bar to ask about seating and a server. Bartender said, "sit wherever the server is around" and turned around to go to the other end of the bar for absolutely no discernible reason whatsoever. The new customer and I made eye contact and had a brief "what is the matter with that guy" exchange.  I had far overstayed what this place was worth and asked to cash out. With only a few other people at the bar and no other responsibilities the bartender could not remember if I had paid for my first drink. My total time in this place was no more than 30 minutes. I had not paid and told him I had not. I can only imagine how much money this guy costs the bar on a busy night if he can't handle four customers at the bar and a small group who ordered a single drink each.  Don't bother. Don't waste your time. If you are following a band here because they have a gig, tell them the alley is a friendlier and better place. Probably less sticky and the dumpsters will have more personality than whoever pencil-behind-the-ear is.

As the bar explained, it does not have outside cameras, so there is nothing to share. Of course, that doesn’t stop the tin foil hat conspiracy theorists from posting their nonsense.
